#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn24.19"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn24.19:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 24 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 24 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 2. Dutiyagamanavagga → gamanavaggo (bj) | dutiyapeyyālo (s1-3) | purimagamanam (aṭṭhārasa-veyyākaraṇāni) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn24.19:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyagamanavagga "
msgstr "2. The Second Round "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn24.19:0.3"
msgid "19. Vātasutta "
msgstr "19. Winds "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn24.19:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:1.2"
msgid "“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on what, does the view arise: "

msgctxt "sn24.19:1.3"
msgid "‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā, esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:1.4"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe … "
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn24.19:2.1"
msgid "“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.19:2.2"
msgid "‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’ "

msgctxt "sn24.19:2.3"
msgid "Vedanāya sati … pe … "
msgstr "When feeling … "

msgctxt "sn24.19:2.4"
msgid "saññāya sati … pe … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn24.19:2.5"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn24.19:2.6"
msgid "viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on consciousness, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.19:2.7"
msgid "‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.218, sc3
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.4"
msgid "api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya—"
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would the view arise: "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.5"
msgid "na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā”ti? "
msgstr "‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.6"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.7"
msgid "“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya, dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati: "
msgstr "“And so, when suffering exists, because of grasping suffering and insisting on suffering, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.8"
msgid "‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’ "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.9"
msgid "“Vedanā … "
msgstr "Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.10"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.13"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante” … pe … vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, "
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.14"
msgid "api nu taṃ anupādāya evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya "
msgstr "“But by not grasping what’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, would such a view arise?” "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.15"
msgid "‘na vātā vāyanti … pe … esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.16"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.17"
msgid "“Iti kho, bhikkhave, dukkhe sati, dukkhaṃ upādāya, dukkhaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjeyya: "
msgstr "“And so, when suffering exists, because of grasping suffering and insisting on suffering, the view arises: "

msgctxt "sn24.19:3.18"
msgid "‘na vātā vāyanti, na najjo sandanti, na gabbhiniyo vijāyanti, na candimasūriyā udenti vā apenti vā, esikaṭṭhāyiṭṭhitā’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Winds don’t blow; rivers don’t flow; pregnant women don’t give birth; the moon and stars neither rise nor set, but stand firm like a pillar.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn24.19:3.19"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

